{
  "texts": [
    "Our results match those of Guo et al. (2023) on the related task of hatespeech detection where few-shot prompting leads to the lowest performance across various prompting techniques used by the researchers.",
    "We now evaluate the content moderation performance of language models on imbalanced datasets, as balanced sampling results in a less challenging distribution than real-time moderation data where the number of removals are typically low (< 10%).",
    "We compute the test metrics at different imbalance thresholds: 1%, 5%, and 10% moderated comments and remaining unmoderated comments.",
    "Due to the possibility of high variance based on the sample, we collate AUC scores for 30 different runs.",
    "We report results here for 2 subreddits-r/changemyview and r/AskRedditwhere the SLMs had the best and the worst performance, respectively, in the balanced setting."
  ]
}